2. Nepenthes dubia is possibly a hybrid between N. inermis and N. bongso (
Danser Bull. Jard. Bot. Buitenzorg III 9 1928 286
). Nepenthes tenuis is included here with some hesitation, the pitcher being somewhat broader in its lower half and the altitude (1000 m) being considerably lower than in the remaining collections, but in other respects it matches N. dubia.

