					spur c. 5 mm long, entire.

Upper pitchers as the lower, but more cylindrical, 7-11.5 by 1.2-2.7 cm;
					wings sparsely fringed near mouth and to 2 mm broad, or lacking fringed elements, 0.4-0.5 mm broad;
					mouth, peristome, lid and spur as in lower pitchers.

