					lid ovate, c. 2.5 by 2.5 cm, apex rounded, base cordate, lower surface usually with two appendages, basal appendage laterally flattened, often hooked towards base, apical appendage usually filiform, up to 12 mm long, rarely reduced to an inconspicuous swollen area, nectar glands sparsely scattered to fairly dense, orbicular, thinly bordered, 0.1-0.2(-0.4) mm diam., along the midline, sparsely scattered, larger, longitudinally elliptic, 0.5(-0.8) mm long, extending to appendages, where dense;
