					spur entire, dorsiventrally flattened, surrounded by filiform appendages.

Upper pitchers subcylindrical, basal 1/3 slightly ventricose, upper 2/3 tubular or slightly attenuate and dilated at the mouth, 12-15 by 2.5-3 cm, with 2 narrow wings 1-3 mm wide, fringed or not, fringe elements up to 3 mm long, up to 2 mm apart;
